## Steps to configure email account in gmail


1.Open your Gmail account.
2. At the top right, click the Settings icon. 
3.Select Settings.
4.Select the Accounts and Import tab.
5. In the Check mail from other accounts (using POP3) section, click Add a POP3 mail account you own.
6.Enter your domain email address, then click Next Step.
7.Enter your account username. Your username is your full email address
8.Enter the email accounts password.
9.Enter your accounts POP server information.

username: enter the email address
password: enter the email password
POP server: mail.domain.com
POP3 port:110 (or use 995 for SSL)

10. Select any additional options you need. 
11. Click the Add Account button.
12. Outgoing mail SMTP. Select the option "Yes I want to be able to send email as "test@domain.com"
13. Click "Add account" button
14. Enter the SMTP server details:

    SMTP server: use webmail address 
    SMTP port: 25 (use port 465 if you select SSL)
    Enter your username, which is your full email address.
    Enter the password of your domain email account.
    

15. click Add Account.

16. Before your domain email account is successfully added, you will need to enter the confirmation code sent to your domain email account. 
    So, open your domain email account and open the confirmation email sent from Google.
    Copy and paste the Google confirmation code into the confirmation window
    
    When ready, click Verify. This will complete the domain email account import process.
